[SN]TITLE[SN]
Homes evacuated as crews tackle Llanelli church fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Homes were evacuated as firefighters tackled a large blaze at a derelict church in Carmarthenshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Crews were called to Park Congregational Church on Murray Street at about 19:00 BST on Thursday after reports of smoke in the tower.
Mid and West Wales Fire and Rescue Service said 20 firefighters would remain at the scene to dampen down.
Murray Street and the surrounding roads were closed for safety reasons but no casualties were reported.
Residents living close to the church were evacuated to Llanelli Leisure Centre and the Vista Lounge restaurant.
Dyfed-Powys Police Insp James Davies said: "The church is well alight and has sustained substantial damage.
"Due to concerns for safety, a large number of properties in the surrounding area have been evacuated and a cordon is in place."
The cause of the fire is being investigated.
